Citations
Date: 0/0/1939
Source: First White Boy Born in Otago
Author: BEATTIE
Vol / Page: 178
Edition:
Quote: The doctor came to the north bank and left his horse, and he and [Jimmy] the Needle double-banked across. The Needle was washed off and the doctor rode to the hut. He must have been `a bit on' to leave the other in the river. ... he was asked `Where's the Needle?' He replied `In Hell!'
