Author: SCANLAN
Vol / Page: 42
Edition: 1949
Quote: As children they had walked along it to school, before they had a pony, on which they`double-banked'. <i>Ibid.</i> 52 They were ready and waiting when the three children returned from school, riding one behind the other on a fat Shetland pony. They still called it `double-banking' though young Nicholas had been added to the load at the beginning of the year.
